01:33.745 --> 01:35.225
it's a bullet train
to the Oval Office.

01:35.269 --> 01:37.880
-Hmm. -Don't you want Ruth
to be the president?

01:37.923 --> 01:40.143
Of course I do,
but you can do it without going

01:40.187 --> 01:42.189
to some pressure cooker
that turns her into a robot.

01:42.232 --> 01:44.321
[in robotic voice]: Meep, meep,
alphabet, meep, meep, numbers.

01:44.365 --> 01:46.410
Have you not seen Star Wars?
Robots are helpful and

01:46.454 --> 01:48.151
-often delightful. -CECE: Please
don't start this again.

01:48.195 --> 01:50.197
You two have been arguing
about how Ruth should be raised

01:50.240 --> 01:51.372
since the day she was born.

01:51.415 --> 01:53.025
SCHMIDT:
I'm sorry, I have to.

01:53.069 --> 01:54.462
Okay, if it was up to her,
Ruth would have been born

01:54.505 --> 01:56.028
in a rusty tub in the Ladies Y.

01:56.072 --> 01:57.465
